{"image_id": "NEE_2006_page_49", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "43", "bbox": [627.1, 1593.5, 647.9, 1612.3]}, {"text": "update these estimates and projections which can affect the annual expense amounts recognized, the liabilities recorded and", "bbox": [112.5, 129.5, 1162.5, 148.3]}, {"text": "the annual funding requirements for nuclear decommissioning costs.  For example, an increase of 0.25% in the assumed", "bbox": [112.5, 151.1, 1162.4, 169.9]}, {"text": "escalation rates would increase FPL Group's and FPL's ARO as of December 31, 2006 by $180 million and $158 million,", "bbox": [112.5, 172.8, 1162.6, 191.5]}, {"text": "respectively.", "bbox": [112.5, 194.4, 216.2, 213.1]}, {"text": "Regulatory Accounting – FPL follows the accounting practices set forth in FAS 71, \"Accounting for the Effects of Certain Types", "bbox": [112.5, 237.6, 1162.5, 256.4]}, {"text": "of Regulation.\"  FAS 71 indicates that regulators can create assets and impose liabilities that would not be recorded by non-", "bbox": [112.5, 259.3, 1162.5, 278.0]}, {"text": "rate regulated entities.  Regulatory assets and liabilities represent probable future revenues that will be recovered from or", "bbox": [112.5, 280.9, 1162.6, 299.6]}, {"text": "refunded to customers through the ratemaking process.  If FPL were no longer subject to cost-based rate regulation, the", "bbox": [112.5, 302.5, 1162.5, 321.2]}, {"text": "existing regulatory assets and liabilities would be written off unless regulators specify an alternative means of recovery or", "bbox": [112.5, 324.1, 1162.5, 342.9]}, {"text": "refund.  In addition, the FPSC has the authority to disallow recovery of costs that it considers excessive or imprudently", "bbox": [112.5, 345.7, 1162.9, 364.5]}, {"text": "incurred.  Such costs may include, among others, O&M expenses, the cost of replacing power lost when fossil and nuclear", "bbox": [112.5, 367.3, 1162.4, 386.1]}, {"text": "units are unavailable, storm restoration costs and costs associated with the construction or acquisition of new facilities.  The", "bbox": [112.5, 389.0, 1162.5, 407.7]}, {"text": "continued applicability of FAS 71 is assessed at each reporting period.", "bbox": [112.5, 410.6, 694.7, 429.3]}, {"text": "Effective December 31, 2006, FPL Group adopted the recognition and disclosure provisions of FAS 158, which requires", "bbox": [112.5, 453.8, 1162.5, 472.6]}, {"text": "reporting of previously unrecognized actuarial gains and losses, prior service costs or credits and transition assets or", "bbox": [112.5, 475.5, 1162.3, 494.2]}, {"text": "obligations related to pension and other post retirement benefits gross on the balance sheet.  The portion of previously", "bbox": [112.5, 497.1, 1162.8, 515.8]}, {"text": "unrecognized actuarial gains and losses, prior service costs or credits and transition assets or obligations that are estimated to", "bbox": [112.5, 518.7, 1162.6, 537.4]}, {"text": "be allocable to FPL as net periodic benefit (income) cost in future periods is classified as regulatory assets and liabilities on", "bbox": [112.5, 540.3, 1162.5, 559.1]}, {"text": "FPL Group's 2006 consolidated balance sheet in accordance with regulatory treatment as required by FAS 71.  See Note 3.", "bbox": [112.5, 561.9, 1134.1, 580.7]}, {"text": "FPL Group's and FPL's regulatory assets and liabilities are as follows:", "bbox": [112.5, 605.2, 672.8, 623.9]}, {"text": "FPL Group", "bbox": [808.4, 648.4, 898.1, 667.2]}, {"text": "FPL", "bbox": [1052.6, 648.4, 1086.5, 667.2]}, {"text": "December 31,", "bbox": [795.9, 672.3, 910.6, 691.0]}, {"text": "December 31,", "bbox": [1012.3, 672.3, 1127.0, 691.0]}, {"text": "2006", "bbox": [776.6, 696.0, 817.4, 714.8]}, {"text": "2005", "bbox": [889.1, 696.0, 929.9, 714.8]}, {"text": "2006", "bbox": [993.0, 696.0, 1033.8, 714.8]}, {"text": "2005", "bbox": [1105.5, 696.0, 1146.2, 714.8]}, {"text": "Regulatory assets:", "bbox": [113.3, 719.8, 263.8, 738.5]}, {"text": "(millions)", "bbox": [925.1, 71